cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on speech enhancement and noise suppression, which falls under the domain of sound processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses the use of objective metrics and subjective tests to evaluate the performance of noise suppression models, which involves natural language processing and computational linguistics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper describes the use of a large clean speech and noise corpus for training noise suppression models, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the development of an online subjective test framework for researchers to quickly test their developments, which involves the design and implementation of a system.
